    <h3 class="title"><a href="/green-u-s-transit-whopping-myth#comment-5829" class="active">It&#039;s an average</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Wed, 2008-07-30 20:13.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>The DOE&#8217;s number is a national average, combining the stop and go with the smooth sailing.  However, it is a valid point (noted to some degree but expanded on) that our current number is based on our current congestion.</p>

<p>Current thinking is that traffic expands to fill the roads.  Build more roads, get more traffic, build fewer, get less.  People adapt.  There is a level beyond which they won&#8217;t take a road if it&#8217;s too gnarly.  They will divert to other roads, or live elsewhere, or take transit.</p>
